text:
Sonoma County restaurants, wineries and bars will no longer be able to serve patrons indoors starting Monday — the latest example of Bay Area counties being directed by the state to curb the spread of coronavirus.

Story by @JohnKingSFChron & @abauman2: https://t.co/JDexbdEc5j

name: sfchronicle
text: The number of people hospitalized with COVID-19 in the nine-county Bay Area hit 578 on Saturday, according to the latest state figures. That’s another record high, up from 567 a day earlier. https://t.co/56L1De899q
